{
  "texts": [
    "An illustration of AI-enabled waveform design for ISAC is shown in Figure 13, where the AI model at the ISAC-BS takes as input the wireless channel H, information symbols s, and reference radar waveform X 0, and outputs the dual-function waveform X.",
    "This mapping can be written as X = f θ (X 0, s, H), (14) where f θ refers to the non-linear mapping function of the AI model with weights θ.Zhong et al. [74] investigated the joint phase-shift and dual-functional waveform design for IRS-aided ISAC networks, where the weighted sum of sensing SINR and MUI power was minimized.",
    "Different from the traditional non-convex optimization algorithms that adopt the alternative optimization framework, they proposed a DNN to optimize all these variables simultaneously, achieving 0.69 dB sensing SINR and 138.8% achievable rate improvement.",
    "Pulkkinen et al. [221] considered a dynamic spectrum sharing scenario with the non-stationary channel and interference, and optimized the dual-functional waveform for interference management.",
    "They proposed a model-free DRL algorithm to learn the dynamic power allocation and sub-carrier selection policy via interacting with the time-varying environment."
  ]
}